  "prompt": "Who was the first teacher in the world?",
  "response": "Identifying the very first teacher in the world is not possible due to the lack of written records from ancient times. However, teaching as a concept likely began when early humans started sharing knowledge and skills necessary for survival, such as hunting, gathering, and tool-making, through observation and communication.\n\nIn a more structured sense, one of the earliest known teachers in recorded history was Confucius (551\u2013479 BCE), a Chinese philosopher who founded Confucianism and taught a broad set of principles on morality, government, and society.\n\nHowever, even before Confucius, there were certainly educators in ancient civilizations like Sumer, Egypt, and India, where scribes and priests often took on the role of teaching new generations.",
